article.description: Desmond Cambridge scored 23 points on Friday night, and Brown pulled away late in the first half and then held on for an 82-74 win over UMass-Lowell.
article.headline: Cambridge scores 23, Brown beats UMass Lowell 82-74
article.linkText: Cambridge scores 23, Brown beats UMass Lowell 82-74
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Desmond Cambridge scored 23 points on Friday night, and Brown pulled away late in the first half and then held on for an 82-74 win over UMass-Lowell. Brandon Anderson added 12 points and six assists, and Chris Sullivan scored 11 for the Bears (1-2). The game was closely contested for the first 14 minutes before Brown scored 14 straight points to build a 43-28 lead late in the first half. The Bears had their largest lead at 47-30 on the opening basket of the second half. The River Hawks (1-3) had a 15-2 run to cut the deficit to 49-45 but Brown pushed the lead to 56-46 and kept the advantage between seven and 13 the rest of the way. Obadiah Noel scored 17, Josh Gantz added 16, Alex Rivera had 13 and Ryan Jones 10 for UMass Lowell.
